Day 5

You work as the IT staff in a company, a new intern Sam started today.You received an email from HR to create Sam in the system with all the necessary credentials.
Create user Sam
Give Sam password Sam#123
Create group interns
Add Sam to the interns group 
Grant group interns read only priviledges to the /tmp folder your created in Day4

NB: Kindly outline the steps you took to finish this task.

-----------
Steps Taken
-----------

I navigated to my root user’s home directory to start the tasks (the alternative is to use sudo command anywhere)
I used (sudo useradd -m sam) to add the new intern as a user
I verified it's success with (ls /home) and (id sam)
I set the password to (Sam#123) using (sudo passwd sam) command
I created a group for interns using (sudo groupadd interns) command
I verified it's success using (getent group interns)
I used (sudo usermod -aG interns sam) to add the user sam to the Interns group
I used (groups sam) or (getent group interns)to verify
I navigated to the directory containing the tmp folder
I used (sudo chown :interns tmp) to change the group ownership to interns
I used (sudo chmod 750 tmp) to set read only permission to the interns group
I used (ls -ld) to confirm changes to tmp permisiions
I used (git add Day5) command to stage the Day5 file
I used (git commit -m "details") to commit Day5 file
I used (git push) to push the files to my remote repo on github